        <h2 class="Heading2"><a name="kanchor110"></a>Fine-tuning auto-scaling</h2>
        <p>You can adjust the number of volumes and their sizes assigned to any processor group in your system. Reallocating resources may help with auto-scaling performance issues.</p>
        <p class="Note">Each process group is associated with a pre-defined <span class="VariablesProductName">DigitalEdge</span> security group. Security groups are managed in the <b>Management Console</b> on the <b>Security</b> page. You must have security group permissions to edit parameters here. </p>
        <p class="Note"> Not all auto-scaling parameters are editable. Grayed-out values cannot be adjusted.</p>
        <ol>
            <li value="1">Open <b>System Builder</b>.</li>
            <li value="2">Go to the <b>Details </b>tab.</li>
            <li value="3">Select a process that needs adjustment.</li>
            <li value="4">Edit parameters that specify your auto-scaling needs<ol><li value="1">Double-click on the value in the <b>Inst Size</b> or <b>Scale?</b> cell and select a new value from the allowable list.</li><li value="2">Double-click on a value in the numeric parameter fields and edit the value:</li></ol></li>
        </ol>
        <ul>
            <li value="1"><b>Min</b>
            </li>
            <li value="2"><b>Max</b>
            </li>
            <li value="3"><b>Alloc</b>
            </li>
            <li value="4"><b>Dealloc</b>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <ol data-mc-continue="true">
            <li value="5">Click <b>Build</b>. <img src="../resources/images/operations/sb_build.png" /></li>
        </ol>
